---
title: Citrus Beef Tacos with Pickled Onion & Southwest Crema
description: The week just isn’t complete without taco night. If you agree (and how could you not?), you’re in luck! Our chefs put together a Tex Mex–style taco that’s sure to satisfy. There’s citrusy pork, bell pepper, and pickled onion, all piled into steamy-soft tortillas. Drizzle it all with a Southwest-spiced crema and you’re ready for a truly spec-TACO-lar meal.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/645a64ed35b69bb140089810-1c093352.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/65395ef1b8cd6bf4c478fc09.pdf
course: main course
nutrition:
  calories: 860 kcal
  fat: 49 g
  saturated fat: 18 g
  carbohydrates: 70 g
  sugar: 21 g
  protein: 34 g
  fiber: 7 g
  sodium: 1610 mg
cuisine: Mexican
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/citrus-beef-tacos-65395ef1b8cd6bf4c478fc09
author: HelloFresh
servings: 2
time required: 30 minutes
---

Wash and dry produce.

Halve, peel, and thinly slice @yellow onion{1}. Quarter @lime{1}. Halve, core, and thinly
slice @long green pepper{1} into strips. Halve @orange{1}. Roughly chop @cilantro{1/4%ounce}.

In a small, #microwave-safe bowl{}, combine ¼ of the onion, juice from
half the lime, @sugar{1/4%tsp} (½ tsp for 4 servings), and a pinch of @salt. Cover
with #plastic wrap{} and microwave for ~{30%seconds}. Set aside.

In a separate small #bowl{}, combine @sour cream{3%tbsp} with @Southwest spice blend{1/4%tsp} (½ tsp for 4).
(You'll use the remaining Southwest Spice Blend later.) Season with salt and @pepper{}. Stir
in @water{} 1 tsp at a time until mixture
reaches a drizzling consistency.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{2%tsp} in a large pan over
medium-high heat. Add green pepper
and remaining onion; cook, stirring
occasionally, until browned and
tender, ~{5-7%minutes}. Season with salt
and pepper.

Turn off heat; transfer to a medium bowl. Wipe out pan.

Heat a drizzle of oil in pan used for
veggies over medium-high heat. Add
@ground beef{10%oz} and remaining
@Southwest spice blend{3/4%tsp}. Cook, breaking up meat
into pieces, until browned, ~{3-4%minutes}.

> TIP: If there's excess grease in your pan, carefully pour it out.

Stir in @Tex-Mex paste{1}, juice from
orange, and a squeeze of lime juice.
Bring to a simmer and cook until
beef is cooked through and sauce has
thickened, ~{2-3%minutes} more. Taste
and season with salt and pepper.

> Swap in turkey or pork for beef.

While beef cooks, wrap @flour tortillas{6} in
damp #paper towels{} and microwave
until warm and pliable, ~{30%seconds}.

Divide tortillas between plates and fill
with beef filling and veggies. Drizzle
with crema and top with pickled
onion (draining first) and cilantro.
Serve with any remaining lime
wedges on the side.

> Ground Beef is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 160°.